# Pin for the bundled backend sidecar, so the packaged .dmg is identical
# machine-to-machine. The Electron build (Scripts/build-electron-mac.sh) verifies
# the backend repo is checked out at SHA below before bundling it.
#
# Bootstrapping: leave SHA empty and run the build once — it records the current
# backend HEAD here and tells you to commit this file. Thereafter every machine
# must build from that exact commit (or the build fails).
#
# Re-pin: set SHA to a new full commit hash and commit this file.
# Override (NOT for release builds): DWELLIUM_ALLOW_BACKEND_DRIFT=1 bypasses the check.
REPO=NovaTrustSolutions/ai-dashboard369-file-manager
SHA=
